FIX: test get default ccache method

This fix according to the change to credential cache since Kerberos 1.10

In Kerberos 1.10, credential cache collection was introduced. The default
credential cache is initilaized in directory /run/user/$UID/krb5cc/

More information about this, refer to
http://web.mit.edu/kerberos/krb5-devel/doc/basic/ccache_def.html#collections-of-caches

Fix repo name

Migrate krbV to python-gssapi

krbContext is totally rewritten with python-gssapi. Major changes:

* krbV is dropped and instead python-gssapi is used.
* There is no module level methods. All original methods are moved to
  krbContext class.
* krbContext can work with with statement as a context manager.
  Meanwhile, it can also be used as a library to initialize credential
  cache by calling API directly.
* init_ccache_as_regular_user is renamed to init_with_password.
* init_ccache_with_keytab is renamed to init_with_keytab.
* No need of kinit command. With gssapi, new parameter password is added
  for the case of initializing with a given password.
* threading Lock is context level now rather than init method level.
* Add requirement of gssapi
* Clean deprecated code.

Fix renewing expired FILE ccache

Renewing expired FILE ccache didn't work because krbcontext created an
empty file for the ccache, but kerberos considered an empty file
invalid.

Fix this by creating a temporary directory and letting kerberos create
the ccache file by itself (which is a perfectly valid scenario). Also
add cleanup for the temporary dir and fix the directory naming.
